<TITLE>OUR PASSPORT TO HEAVEN</TITLE>


<TEXT>
Sir, 

Since my teen years, I have always had this voracious and insatiable appetite for reading. 
 

I also had this passion of one <TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DURATION" value="PXD">day</TIMEX3> writing something that would <EVENT eid="e1" class="OCCURRENCE">make</EVENT> people <EVENT eid="e2" class="OCCURRENCE">sit</EVENT> up and <EVENT eid="e3" class="OCCURRENCE">read</EVENT>. 
I am <EVENT eid="e4" class="I_STATE">grateful</EVENT> to the Times <TIMEX3 tid="t2" type="DATE" value="2017-01-29">SUNDAY</TIMEX3> editor for <EVENT eid="e5" class="OCCURRENCE">availing</EVENT> me that opportunity on numerous occasions, in <TIMEX3 tid="t3" type="DATE" value="PAST_REF">the past</TIMEX3>, to <EVENT eid="e6" class="OCCURRENCE">share</EVENT> my life experiences. 
 

I do <EVENT eid="e7" class="I_STATE">concede</EVENT> that I am fallible, like all men and may <EVENT eid="e8" class="OCCURRENCE">err</EVENT> here and there but I always <EVENT eid="e9" class="I_ACTION">endeavour</EVENT> to <EVENT eid="e10" class="OCCURRENCE">ask</EVENT> God to <EVENT eid="e11" class="OCCURRENCE">give</EVENT> me the wisdom to <EVENT eid="e12" class="OCCURRENCE">share</EVENT> some of His truths. 
These truths need to be <EVENT eid="e13" class="OCCURRENCE">shared</EVENT> with and by all because we are incessantly and rapidly <EVENT eid="e14" class="OCCURRENCE">approaching</EVENT> our final appointment with our Creator and whether we <EVENT eid="e15" class="OCCURRENCE">like</EVENT> it or not, will be compelled to <EVENT eid="e16" class="OCCURRENCE">account</EVENT> for our every deeds  both good and bad, while we <EVENT eid="e17" class="OCCURRENCE">journeyed</EVENT> on this earth. 
 
One publication that is <EVENT eid="e18" class="I_STATE">keeping</EVENT> me <EVENT eid="e19" class="OCCURRENCE">engrossed</EVENT> lately is that age-old Book of Wisdom, <EVENT eid="e20" class="OCCURRENCE">penned</EVENT> <TIMEX3 tid="t4" type="DURATION" value="PXY">years ago</TIMEX3> by diverse men who were <EVENT eid="e21" class="OCCURRENCE">inspired</EVENT> by Gods Holy spirit to <EVENT eid="e22" class="OCCURRENCE">write</EVENT>. This is the Bible. 
Many of us own this remarkable book but we only <EVENT eid="e23" class="OCCURRENCE">read</EVENT> a few pages of it. 
 

We <EVENT eid="e24" class="I_STATE">forget</EVENT> that this Book is our passport to being considered worthy of being <EVENT eid="e25" class="OCCURRENCE">accepted</EVENT> in Gods heavenly kingdom. 
If you <EVENT eid="e26" class="I_ACTION">happen</EVENT> to <EVENT eid="e27" class="OCCURRENCE">read</EVENT> many prophecies of the Bible, do you <EVENT eid="e28" class="I_STATE">happen</EVENT> to <EVENT eid="e29" class="OCCURRENCE">read</EVENT> Matthew saccount of Christs Olivet prophecy in Chapter 24 verse 6, about the unprecedented preaching of Gods Word as one of the signs that we are <TIMEX3 tid="t5" type="DATE" value="PRESENT_REF">now</TIMEX3> in the very last stages of earths calendar? 
 

Let us <EVENT eid="e30" class="OCCURRENCE">read</EVENT> Matthews account: 
And this gospel of the kingdom will be <EVENT eid="e31" class="OCCURRENCE">preached</EVENT> in the whole world as a testimony to all nations, and then the end will <EVENT eid="e32" class="OCCURRENCE">come</EVENT>. 
Take note of the words as a testimony.These really <EVENT eid="e33" class="OCCURRENCE">caught</EVENT> my eye. 
 

One does not <EVENT eid="e34" class="I_STATE">need</EVENT> not to be a rocket scientist to <EVENT eid="e35" class="STATE">discern</EVENT> that whether we <EVENT eid="e36" class="I_ACTION">choose</EVENT> to <EVENT eid="e37" class="OCCURRENCE">ignore</EVENT> it or not, the magnitude of the <EVENT eid="e38" class="OCCURRENCE">preaching</EVENT> of Gods Word in the whole world has <EVENT eid="e39" class="OCCURRENCE">reached</EVENT> such overwhelming and glorious levels. 
This is testimony to both believers and non-believers alike, that something is <EVENT eid="e40" class="OCCURRENCE">brewing</EVENT> in the air and that many of us, by deliberately ignoring the preaching of the Word on radio, television, churches, in the streets, through the internet, in many crusades, revivals - you name it, when we stand before the judgement seat of God, no one will have any excuse that the Word was not <EVENT eid="e41" class="OCCURRENCE">preached</EVENT> to him or her. 
 

Revelation 14 verse 6 <EVENT eid="e42" class="OCCURRENCE">reveals</EVENT> further testimony and a very sombre warning about an angel <EVENT eid="e43" class="OCCURRENCE">flying</EVENT> in the air, <EVENT eid="e44" class="OCCURRENCE">proclaiming</EVENT> these chilling words: 
Then I saw another angel flying in midair and he had the eternal gospel to <EVENT eid="e45" class="OCCURRENCE">proclaim</EVENT> to those who live on earth  to every nation, tribe, language and people. 
The eternal Word of God is not limited to being <EVENT eid="e46" class="OCCURRENCE">preached</EVENT> in Swaziland only but in every nook and cranny of the world and in many languages. 
It is available in some places at a nominal fee, at times free and to all those who thirst for spiritual truths  at no cost! 
 

Sadly, we <EVENT eid="e47" class="I_ACTION">choose</EVENT> to <EVENT eid="e48" class="OCCURRENCE">ignore</EVENT> it and <EVENT eid="e49" class="OCCURRENCE">leave</EVENT> our bibles in our room dividers or cupboards to <EVENT eid="e50" class="OCCURRENCE">gather</EVENT> dust without <EVENT eid="e51" class="OCCURRENCE">bothering</EVENT> to page through. 
We <EVENT eid="e52" class="OCCURRENCE">ignore</EVENT> the fact that time is <EVENT eid="e53" class="OCCURRENCE">running</EVENT> out fast for many of us and we <EVENT eid="e54" class="OCCURRENCE">lose</EVENT> sight of the fact that our appointment with eternity is just on the horizon. 
 

Why do many of us <EVENT eid="e55" class="I_ACTION">choose</EVENT> to <EVENT eid="e56" class="OCCURRENCE">ignore</EVENT> such valuable wisdom? I have no doubt that the hand of Satan is <EVENT eid="e57" class="OCCURRENCE">playing</EVENT> a very major role in many minds, <EVENT eid="e58" class="I_ACTION">influencing</EVENT> us to <EVENT eid="e59" class="OCCURRENCE">disregard</EVENT> Gods Word and <EVENT eid="e60" class="OCCURRENCE">view</EVENT> it as boring and a waste of time. 
Satan is very adept at <EVENT eid="e61" class="OCCURRENCE">blinding</EVENT> many minds because he is, since his fall from Eden, very intent on <EVENT eid="e62" class="OCCURRENCE">preventing</EVENT> us from <EVENT eid="e63" class="OCCURRENCE">seeing</EVENT> the light of the gospel, which <EVENT eid="e64" class="OCCURRENCE">has</EVENT> the propensity to <EVENT eid="e65" class="OCCURRENCE">change</EVENT> our lives and <EVENT eid="e66" class="OCCURRENCE">enable</EVENT> us to be spiritually linked to the heavenly kingdom. 
<EVENT eid="e67" class="I_STATE">Remember</EVENT> that he was <EVENT eid="e68" class="OCCURRENCE">cast</EVENT> out from heaven, in the process <EVENT eid="e69" class="OCCURRENCE">taking</EVENT> with him a third of the angels because of pride, as a result of his malicious intent of wanting to be like the Most High God. 

Alex Lucky Nxumalo 
MANZINI
</TEXT>


